  <front>
   <head>TO A CERTAIN AUTHOR, ON HIS WRITING A PROLOGUE, WHEREIN HE DESCRIBES A TRAVELLER FROZEN IN A SNOW STORM.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">more let poets vainly boast</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Their fine descriptive art,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They ransack Nature's gayest store,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Yet rarely warm the heart.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Hail, happy Bard, whose brilliant wit,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With more than Poet's art,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Can from a frozen mass extract</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Fire that can melt the heart.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
